il|Prisoner of war mail]]\n* [[Prison escape]]\n* [[Prisoner-of-war camp]]\n* [[Prisoner of War Medal]] U.S. decortion, includes synposis of Congressional discussion on how to define a P.O.W.\n* [[Prisoner of War Medal 1940\u20131945]] Belgian award\n* [[Rule of Law in Armed Conflicts Project (RULAC)]]\n* [[Tom Walsh (Wyoming politician)|Thomas E. \"Tom\" Walsh, Sr.]]\n* [[The United States Military Code of Conduct]]\n* [[Vietnam War POW/MIA issue]]\n* [[War crime]]\n* [[World War I prisoners of war in Germany]]\n* [[World War II Radio Heroes: Letters of Compassion]]\n{{colend}}\n\n==References==\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n* [[Rule of Law in Armed Conflicts Project (RULAC)]]\n* [[Johnny Hickman|John Hickman]], \"What is a Prisoner of War For?\" ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20070205204548/http://academic.sun.ac.za/mil/mil_history/scientia%20militaria.htm Scientia Militaria: South African Journal of Military Studies]''. Vol. 36, No. 2. 2008. pp.&nbsp;19\u201335.\n* [[s:Third Geneva Convention|Full text of Third Geneva Convention, 1949 revision]]\n* {{cite encyclopedia | encyclopedia=Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica | edition=CD | year=2002 | article=Prisoner of War}}\n* [http://www.gendercide.org/case_soviet.html Gendercide site]\n* \"Soviet Casualties and Combat Losses in the Twentieth Century\", Greenhill Books, London, 1997, G. F. Krivosheev, editor.\n* \"Keine Kameraden. Die Wehrmacht und die sowjetischen Kriegsgefangenen 1941\u20131945\", Dietz, Bonn 1997, {{ISBN|3-8012-5023-7}}\n* Bligh, Alexander. 2015. \"The 1973 War and the Formation of Israeli POW Policy \u2013 A Watershed Line? \". In Udi Lebel and Eyal Lewin (eds.), The 1973 Yom Kippur War and the Reshaping of Israeli Civil\u2013Military Relations. Washington, DC: Lexington Books (2015), 121\u2013146.\n* Bligh, Alexander. 2014. \"The development of Israel's POW policy: The 1967 War as a test case\", Paper presented at the Seventh Annual ASMEA Conference: Searching for Balance in the Mid