cept include the addition of wing mirrors, an active rear wing and a redesigned rear glass. The car features a double wish-bone suspension system with hydraulic dampers and torque vectoring for improved handling. Stopping power is handled by a carbon-ceramic braking system featuring 10-piston calipers in the front and 4-piston calipers at the rear.<ref name=\"CNET\"/>\n\nThe OWL can accelerate from 0-{{convert|97|kph|mph|0|abbr=on}} in 1.69 seconds, 0-{{convert|100|kph|mph|0|abbr=on}} in 1.9 seconds, 0-{{convert|186|mph|kph|0|abbr=on|order=flip}} in 10.6 seconds and can attain a top speed of {{convert|400|kph|mph|0|abbr=on}}. The OWL's acceleration times make it the fastest accelerating production car in the world.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.topgear.com/car-news/dubai-motor-show/2012bhp-aspark-owl-most-powerful-production-hypercar|title=The 2,012bhp Aspark Owl is the most powerful production hypercar|date=12 November 2019|first=Vijay|last=Pattni|magazine=[[Top Gear (magazine)|Top Gear]]|accessdate=13 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==In Video Games== \n*This Vehicle Will Be Added In [[Asphalt 8: Airborne]]'s \"2020 Spring Update\" And Possible An Class A Or Class S Car.\n\n==Trivia== \n*With Rating Of 2,065 HP, The Aspark Owl Has Highest Horsepower Rating Of Any Other Concept Hypercars, Higher Than [[Ferrari SF90 Stradale]]'s 990 HP, [[McLaren Senna]]'s 795 HP & Along With Both Bugatti & Koenigsegg Cars (Both 1,499 & 1,600 HP).\n*The Aspark Owl Is The First Hypercar To Produced To More Than 2,000 HP (That Is Not Bugatti Or Koenigsegg).\n*The Acura/Honda NSX 2nd Gen, Mazda Furai & Aspark Owl Are The Modern Japanese Rear-Mid Engined Cars.\n*This Is First Electric Hypercar To Produced In Japan.\n*This Is The First Concept Hypercar To Built In 2020s.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* \u682a\u5f0f\u4f1a\u793e\u30a2\u30b9\u30d1\u30fc\u30afR&D\u4e8b\u696d\u90e8 (Aspark R&D), {{youtube|z8PZZAkrIuc|\u3010PV\u3011ASPARK owl}} (September 2017)\n* 